quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  15,91,"who split the Qur'an into bits."
  15,92,"So, by your Lord, We shall question them all,"
  15,93,"about what they have been doing."
  15,94,"Now, proclaim what you are commanded to and turn away from the mushriks (polytheists)."
  15,95,"Surely, We are sufficient for you against those who deride,"
  15,96,"those who take to another god along with Allah. So, they shall soon learn."
  15,97,"And We know that your heart feels distressed for what they say."
  15,98,"So, proclaim the purity, and glory of your Lord and be among those who prostrate."
  15,99,"And worship your Lord until comes to you that which is certain."
  16,1,"The command of Allah is bound to come. So, do not ask for it to come sooner. Pure is He, and much higher than what they ascribe to Him as partners."
  16,2,"He sends down the angels at His behest with the spirit, (that is, the revelation), upon whom He wills from among His servants: 'Warn people that there is no god but Me. So, fear Me.'"
  16,3,"He created the heavens and the earth in the proper way. He is much higher than what they ascribe to Him as partners."
  16,4,"He created man from a drop, and soon he turned into a quarrelsome person expressing himself openly."
  16,5,"As for the cattle, He created them, having warmth for you, and other benefits; and of them you eat."
  16,6,"And for you there is beauty in them when you drive them (home) in the evening and take them out to graze."